tm-swords-dance.name: TM006: Swords Dance
tm-swords-dance.description: A frenetic dance to uplift the fighting spirit. This sharply raises the user's Attack stat.

tm-cut.name: TM007: Cut
tm-cut.description: The target is cut with a scythe or claw.

tm-fly.name: TM008: Fly
tm-fly.description: The user flies up into the sky and then strikes its target on the next turn.

tm-pin-missile.name: TM013: Pin Missile
tm-pin-missile.description: Sharp spikes are shot at the target in rapid succession. They hit two to five times in a row.

tm-roar.name: TM014: Roar
tm-roar.description: The target is scared off, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

tm-low-kick.name: TM022: Low Kick
tm-low-kick.description: A powerful low kick that makes the target fall over. The heavier the target, the greater the move's power.

tm-counter.name: TM023: Counter
tm-counter.description: A retaliation move that counters any physical attack, inflicting double the damage taken.

tm-fire-spin.name: TM026: Fire Spin
tm-fire-spin.description: The target becomes trapped within a fierce vortex of fire that rages for four to five turns.

tm-thunder-wave.name: TM028: Thunder Wave
tm-thunder-wave.description: The user launches a weak jolt of electricity that paralyzes the target.

tm-agility.name: TM034: Agility
tm-agility.description: The user relaxes and lightens its body to move faster. This sharply raises the Speed stat.

tm-night-shade.name: TM035: Night Shade
tm-night-shade.description: The user makes the target see a frightening mirage. It inflicts damage equal to the user's level.

tm-screech.name: TM036: Screech
tm-screech.description: An earsplitting screech harshly lowers the target's Defense stat.

tm-double-team.name: TM037: Double Team
tm-double-team.description: By moving rapidly, the user makes illusory copies of itself to raise its evasiveness.

tm-confuse-ray.name: TM038: Confuse Ray
tm-confuse-ray.description: The target is exposed to a sinister ray that triggers confusion.

tm-light-screen.name: TM039: Light Screen
tm-light-screen.description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from special attacks for five turns.

tm-haze.name: TM040: Haze
tm-haze.description: The user creates a haze that eliminates every stat change among all the Pokémon engaged in battle.

tm-reflect.name: TM041: Reflect
tm-reflect.description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from physical attacks for five turns.

tm-focus-energy.name: TM042: Focus Energy
tm-focus-energy.description: The user takes a deep breath and focuses so that critical hits land more easily.

tm-metronome.name: TM043: Metronome
tm-metronome.description: The user waggles a finger and stimulates its brain into randomly using nearly any move.

tm-swift.name: TM047: Swift
tm-swift.description: Star-shaped rays are shot at opposing Pokémon. This attack never misses.

tm-amnesia.name: TM048: Amnesia
tm-amnesia.description: The user temporarily empties its mind to forget its concerns. This sharply raises the user's Sp. Def stat.

tm-flash.name: TM051: Flash
tm-flash.description: The user flashes a bright light that cuts the target's accuracy.

tm-rest.name: TM053: Rest
tm-rest.description: The user goes to sleep for two turns. This fully restores the user's HP and heals any status conditions.

tm-super-fang.name: TM056: Super Fang
tm-super-fang.description: The user chomps hard on the target with its sharp front fangs. This cuts the target's HP in half.

tm-substitute.name: TM057: Substitute
tm-substitute.description: The user creates a substitute for itself using some of its HP. The substitute serves as the user's decoy.

tm-snore.name: TM059: Snore
tm-snore.description: This attack can be used only if the user is asleep. The harsh noise may also make the target flinch.

tm-curse.name: TM060: Curse
tm-curse.description: A move that works differently for the Ghost type than for all other types.

tm-reversal.name: TM061: Reversal
tm-reversal.description: An all-out attack that becomes more powerful the less HP the user has.

tm-spite.name: TM062: Spite
tm-spite.description: The user unleashes its grudge on the move last used by the target by cutting 4 PP from it.

tm-protect.name: TM063: Protect
tm-protect.description: This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

tm-scary-face.name: TM064: Scary Face
tm-scary-face.description: The user frightens the target with a scary face to harshly lower its Speed stat.

tm-mud-slap.name: TM066: Mud-Slap
tm-mud-slap.description: The user hurls mud in the target's face to inflict damage and lower its accuracy.

tm-spikes.name: TM067: Spikes
tm-spikes.description: The user lays a trap of spikes at the opposing team's feet. The trap hurts Pokémon that switch into battle.

tm-sandstorm.name: TM070: Sandstorm
tm-sandstorm.description: A five-turn sandstorm is summoned to hurt all combatants except Rock, Ground, and Steel types. It raises the Sp. Def stat of Rock types.

tm-endure.name: TM072: Endure
tm-endure.description: The user endures any attack with at least 1 HP. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

tm-charm.name: TM073: Charm
tm-charm.description: The user gazes at the target rather charmingly, making it less wary. This harshly lowers the target's Attack stat.

tm-false-swipe.name: TM074: False Swipe
tm-false-swipe.description: A restrained attack that prevents the target from fainting. The target is left with at least 1 HP.

tm-swagger.name: TM075: Swagger
tm-swagger.description: The user enrages and confuses the target. However, this also sharply raises the target's Attack stat.

tm-attract.name: TM077: Attract
tm-attract.description: If it is the opposite gender of the user, the target becomes infatuated and less likely to attack.

tm-sleep-talk.name: TM078: Sleep Talk
tm-sleep-talk.description: While it is asleep, the user randomly uses one of the moves it knows.

tm-heal-bell.name: TM079: Heal Bell
tm-heal-bell.description: The user makes a soothing bell chime to heal the status conditions of all the party Pokémon.

tm-frustration.name: TM081: Frustration
tm-frustration.description: This full-power attack grows more powerful the less the user likes its Trainer.

tm-safeguard.name: TM082: Safeguard
tm-safeguard.description: The user creates a protective field that prevents status conditions for five turns.

tm-pain-split.name: TM083: Pain Split
tm-pain-split.description: The user adds its HP to the target's HP, then equally shares the combined HP with the target.

tm-baton-pass.name: TM085: Baton Pass
tm-baton-pass.description: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting and passes along any stat changes.

tm-encore.name: TM086: Encore
tm-encore.description: The user compels the target to keep using the move it encored for three turns.

tm-metal-claw.name: TM088: Metal Claw
tm-metal-claw.description: The target is raked with steel claws. This may also raise the user's Attack stat.

tm-rain-dance.name: TM091: Rain Dance
tm-rain-dance.description: The user summons a heavy rain that falls for five turns, powering up Water-type moves. It lowers the power of Fire-type moves.

tm-sunny-day.name: TM092: Sunny Day
tm-sunny-day.description: The user intensifies the sun for five turns, powering up Fire-type moves. It lowers the power of Water-type moves.

tm-psych-up.name: TM094: Psych Up
tm-psych-up.description: The user hypnotizes itself into copying any stat change made by the target.

tm-rock-smash.name: TM097: Rock Smash
tm-rock-smash.description: The user attacks with a punch. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tm-whirlpool.name: TM098: Whirlpool
tm-whirlpool.description: The user traps the target in a violent swirling whirlpool for four to five turns.

tm-beat-up.name: TM099: Beat Up
tm-beat-up.description: The user gets all party Pokémon to attack the target. The more party Pokémon, the greater the number of attacks.

tm-hail.name: TM102: Hail
tm-hail.description: The user summons a hailstorm lasting five turns. It damages all Pokémon except Ice types.

tm-torment.name: TM103: Torment
tm-torment.description: The user torments and enrages the target, making it incapable of using the same move twice in a row.

tm-will-o-wisp.name: TM104: Will-O-Wisp
tm-will-o-wisp.description: The user shoots a sinister flame at the target to inflict a burn.

tm-focus-punch.name: TM106: Focus Punch
tm-focus-punch.description: The user focuses its mind before launching a punch. This move fails if the user is hit before it is used.

tm-nature-power.name: TM107: Nature Power
tm-nature-power.description: This attack makes use of nature's power. Its effects vary depending on the user's environment.

tm-charge.name: TM108: Charge
tm-charge.description: The user boosts the power of the Electric move it uses on the next turn. This also raises the user's Sp. Def stat.

tm-taunt.name: TM109: Taunt
tm-taunt.description: The target is taunted into a rage that allows it to use only attack moves for three turns.

tm-helping-hand.name: TM110: Helping Hand
tm-helping-hand.description: The user assists an ally by boosting the power of that ally's attack.

tm-trick.name: TM111: Trick
tm-trick.description: The user catches the target off guard and swaps its held item with its own.

tm-recycle.name: TM113: Recycle
tm-recycle.description: The user recycles a held item that has been used in battle so it can be used again.

tm-endeavor.name: TM117: Endeavor
tm-endeavor.description: This attack move cuts down the target's HP to equal the user's HP.

tm-skill-swap.name: TM118: Skill Swap
tm-skill-swap.description: The user employs its psychic power to exchange Abilities with the target.

tm-imprison.name: TM119: Imprison
tm-imprison.description: If opposing Pokémon know any move also known by the user, they are prevented from using it.

tm-feather-dance.name: TM121: Feather Dance
tm-feather-dance.description: The user covers the target's body with a mass of down that harshly lowers its Attack stat.

tm-weather-ball.name: TM126: Weather Ball
tm-weather-ball.description: This attack move varies in power and type depending on the weather.

tm-fake-tears.name: TM127: Fake Tears
tm-fake-tears.description: The user feigns crying to fluster the target, harshly lowering its Sp. Def stat.

tm-air-cutter.name: TM128: Air Cutter
tm-air-cutter.description: The user launches razor-like wind to slash opposing Pokémon. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-metal-sound.name: TM131: Metal Sound
tm-metal-sound.description: A horrible sound like scraping metal harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-cosmic-power.name: TM132: Cosmic Power
tm-cosmic-power.description: The user absorbs a mystical power from space to raise its Defense and Sp. Def stats.

tm-sand-tomb.name: TM134: Sand Tomb
tm-sand-tomb.description: The user traps the target inside a harshly raging sandstorm for four to five turns.

tm-bulk-up.name: TM142: Bulk Up
tm-bulk-up.description: The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body, raising both its Attack and Defense stats.

tm-water-pulse.name: TM153: Water Pulse
tm-water-pulse.description: The user attacks the target with a pulsing blast of water. This may also confuse the target.

tm-gravity.name: TM155: Gravity
tm-gravity.description: This move enables Flying-type Pokémon or Pokémon with the Levitate Ability to be hit by Ground-type moves. Moves that involve flying can't be used.

tm-gyro-ball.name: TM156: Gyro Ball
tm-gyro-ball.description: The user tackles the target with a high-speed spin. The slower the user compared to the target, the greater the move's power.

tm-payback.name: TM162: Payback
tm-payback.description: The user stores power, then attacks. If the user moves after the target, this attack's power will be doubled.

tm-assurance.name: TM163: Assurance
tm-assurance.description: If the target has already taken some damage in the same turn, this attack's power is doubled.

tm-embargo.name: TM164: Embargo
tm-embargo.description: This move prevents the target from using its held item for five turns. Its Trainer is also prevented from using items on it.

tm-fling.name: TM165: Fling
tm-fling.description: The user flings its held item at the target to attack. This move's power and effects depend on the item.

tm-power-swap.name: TM167: Power Swap
tm-power-swap.description: The user employs its psychic power to switch changes to its Attack and Sp. Atk stats with the target.

tm-guard-swap.name: TM168: Guard Swap
tm-guard-swap.description: The user employs its psychic power to switch changes to its Defense and Sp. Def stats with the target.

tm-rock-polish.name: TM173: Rock Polish
tm-rock-polish.description: The user polishes its body to reduce drag. This sharply raises the Speed stat.

tm-vacuum-wave.name: TM184: Vacuum Wave
tm-vacuum-wave.description: The user whirls its fists to send a wave of pure vacuum at the target. This move always goes first.

tm-nasty-plot.name: TM190: Nasty Plot
tm-nasty-plot.description: The user stimulates its brain by thinking bad thoughts. This sharply raises the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-defog.name: TM200: Defog
tm-defog.description: A strong wind blows away the target's barriers such as Reflect or Light Screen. This also lowers the target's evasiveness.

tm-trick-room.name: TM201: Trick Room
tm-trick-room.description: The user creates a bizarre area in which slower Pokémon get to move first for five turns.

tm-stealth-rock.name: TM209: Stealth Rock
tm-stealth-rock.description: The user lays a trap of levitating stones around the opposing team. The trap hurts opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

tm-hone-claws.name: TM213: Hone Claws
tm-hone-claws.description: The user sharpens its claws to boost its Attack stat and accuracy.

tm-wonder-room.name: TM214: Wonder Room
tm-wonder-room.description: The user creates a bizarre area in which Pokémon's Defense and Sp. Def stats are swapped for five turns.

tm-magic-room.name: TM217: Magic Room
tm-magic-room.description: The user creates a bizarre area in which Pokémon's held items lose their effects for five turns.

tm-smack-down.name: TM218: Smack Down
tm-smack-down.description: The user throws a stone or similar projectile to attack the target. A flying Pokémon will fall to the ground when it's hit.

tm-acid-spray.name: TM224: Acid Spray
tm-acid-spray.description: The user spits fluid that works to melt the target. This harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-round.name: TM226: Round
tm-round.description: The user attacks the target with a song. Others can join in the Round to increase the power of the attack.

tm-echoed-voice.name: TM227: Echoed Voice
tm-echoed-voice.description: The user attacks the target with an echoing voice. If this move is used every turn, its power is increased.

tm-stored-power.name: TM228: Stored Power
tm-stored-power.description: The user attacks the target with stored power. The more the user's stats are raised, the greater the move's power.

tm-ally-switch.name: TM229: Ally Switch
tm-ally-switch.description: The user teleports using a strange power and switches places with one of its allies.

tm-sky-drop.name: TM232: Sky Drop
tm-sky-drop.description: The user takes the target into the sky, then drops it during the next turn. The target cannot attack while in the sky.

tm-quash.name: TM234: Quash
tm-quash.description: The user suppresses the target and makes its move go last.

tm-struggle-bug.name: TM241: Struggle Bug
tm-struggle-bug.description: While resisting, the user attacks opposing Pokémon. This lowers the Sp. Atk stats of those hit.

tm-work-up.name: TM245: Work Up
tm-work-up.description: The user is roused, and its Attack and Sp. Atk stats increase.

tm-snarl.name: TM254: Snarl
tm-snarl.description: The user yells as if it's ranting about something, which lowers the Sp. Atk stats of opposing Pokémon.

tm-grassy-terrain.name: TM259: Grassy Terrain
tm-grassy-terrain.description: The user turns the ground to grass for five turns. This restores the HP of Pokémon on the ground a little every turn and powers up Grass-type moves.

tm-misty-terrain.name: TM260: Misty Terrain
tm-misty-terrain.description: This protects Pokémon on the ground from status conditions and halves damage from Dragon-type moves for five turns.

tm-confide.name: TM262: Confide
tm-confide.description: The user tells the target a secret, and the target loses its ability to concentrate. This lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-eerie-impulse.name: TM264: Eerie Impulse
tm-eerie-impulse.description: The user's body generates an eerie impulse. Exposing the target to it harshly lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-venom-drench.name: TM265: Venom Drench
tm-venom-drench.description: Opposing Pokémon are drenched in an odd poisonous liquid. This lowers the Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats of a poisoned target.

tm-electric-terrain.name: TM266: Electric Terrain
tm-electric-terrain.description: The user electrifies the ground for five turns, powering up Electric-type moves. Pokémon on the ground no longer fall asleep.

tm-infestation.name: TM268: Infestation
tm-infestation.description: The target is infested and attacked for four to five turns. The target can't flee during this time.

tm-psychic-terrain.name: TM275: Psychic Terrain
tm-psychic-terrain.description: This protects Pokémon on the ground from priority moves and powers up Psychic-type moves for five turns.

tm-speed-swap.name: TM277: Speed Swap
tm-speed-swap.description: The user exchanges Speed stats with the target.

tm-brutal-swing.name: TM279: Brutal Swing
tm-brutal-swing.description: The user swings its body around violently to inflict damage on everything in its vicinity.

tm-aurora-veil.name: TM280: Aurora Veil
tm-aurora-veil.description: This move reduces damage from physical and special moves for five turns. This can be used only when it is snowing.

tm-steel-roller.name: TM288: Steel Roller
tm-steel-roller.description: The user attacks while destroying the terrain. This move fails when the ground hasn't turned into a terrain.

tm-misty-explosion.name: TM291: Misty Explosion
tm-misty-explosion.description: The user attacks everything around it and faints upon using this move. This move's power is increased on Misty Terrain.

tm-grassy-glide.name: TM292: Grassy Glide
tm-grassy-glide.description: Gliding on the ground, the user attacks the target. This move always goes first on Grassy Terrain.

tm-rising-voltage.name: TM293: Rising Voltage
tm-rising-voltage.description: The user attacks with electric voltage rising from the ground. This move's power doubles when the target is on Electric Terrain.

tm-terrain-pulse.name: TM294: Terrain Pulse
tm-terrain-pulse.description: The user utilizes the power of the terrain to attack. This move's type and power changes depending on the terrain when it's used.

tm-corrosive-gas.name: TM299: Corrosive Gas
tm-corrosive-gas.description: The user surrounds everything around it with highly acidic gas and melts away items they hold.

tm-coaching.name: TM300: Coaching
tm-coaching.description: The user properly coaches its ally Pokémon, boosting their Attack and Defense stats.

tm-flip-turn.name: TM301: Flip Turn
tm-flip-turn.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tm-triple-axel.name: TM302: Triple Axel
tm-triple-axel.description: A consecutive three-kick attack that becomes more powerful with each successful hit.

tm-dual-wingbeat.name: TM303: Dual Wingbeat
tm-dual-wingbeat.description: The user slams the target with its wings. The target is hit twice in a row.

tm-snowscape.name: TM307: Snowscape
tm-snowscape.description: The user summons a snowstorm lasting five turns. This boosts the Defense stats of Ice types.

tm-pounce.name: TM308: Pounce
tm-pounce.description: The user attacks by pouncing on the target. This also lowers the target's Speed stat.

tm-trailblaze.name: TM309: Trailblaze
tm-trailblaze.description: The user attacks suddenly as if leaping out from tall grass. The user's nimble footwork boosts its Speed stat.

tm-chilling-water.name: TM310: Chilling Water
tm-chilling-water.description: The user attacks the target by showering it with water that's so cold it saps the target's power. This also lowers the target's Attack stat.

tm-dragon-cheer.name: TM312: Dragon Cheer
tm-dragon-cheer.description: The user raises its allies' morale with a draconic cry so that their future attacks have a heightened chance of landing critical hits. This rouses Dragon types more.

tm-upper-hand.name: TM317: Upper Hand
tm-upper-hand.description: The user reacts to the target's movement and strikes with the heel of its palm, making the target flinch. This move fails if the target is not readying a priority move.

tm-mega-punch.name: TM001: Mega Punch
tm-mega-punch.description: The target is slugged by a punch thrown with muscle-packed power.

tm-fire-punch.name: TM003: Fire Punch
tm-fire-punch.description: The target is punched with a fiery fist. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm-ice-punch.name: TM004: Ice Punch
tm-ice-punch.description: The target is punched with an icy fist. This may also leave the target frozen.

tm-thunder-punch.name: TM005: Thunder Punch
tm-thunder-punch.description: The target is punched with an electrified fist. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm-mega-kick.name: TM009: Mega Kick
tm-mega-kick.description: The target is attacked by a kick launched with muscle-packed power.

tm-body-slam.name: TM010: Body Slam
tm-body-slam.description: The user drops onto the target with its full body weight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm-take-down.name: TM011: Take Down
tm-take-down.description: A reckless, full-body charge attack for slamming into the target. This also damages the user a little.

tm-psybeam.name: TM020: Psybeam
tm-psybeam.description: The target is attacked with a peculiar ray. This may also leave the target confused.

tm-strength.name: TM024: Strength
tm-strength.description: The target is slugged with a punch thrown at maximum power.

tm-dig.name: TM031: Dig
tm-dig.description: The user burrows into the ground, then attacks on the next turn.

tm-toxic.name: TM032: Toxic
tm-toxic.description: A move that leaves the target badly poisoned. Its poison damage worsens every turn.

tm-self-destruct.name: TM044: Self-Destruct
tm-self-destruct.description: The user attacks everything around it by causing an explosion. The user faints upon using this move.

tm-waterfall.name: TM046: Waterfall
tm-waterfall.description: The user charges at the target and may make it flinch.

tm-dream-eater.name: TM049: Dream Eater
tm-dream-eater.description: The user eats the dreams of a sleeping target. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

tm-explosion.name: TM052: Explosion
tm-explosion.description: The user attacks everything around it by causing a tremendous explosion. The user faints upon using this move.

tm-rock-slide.name: TM054: Rock Slide
tm-rock-slide.description: Large boulders are hurled at opposing Pokémon to inflict damage. This may also make the opposing Pokémon flinch.

tm-thief.name: TM058: Thief
tm-thief.description: The user attacks and has a 30% chance to steal the target's held item simultaneously.

tm-icy-wind.name: TM068: Icy Wind
tm-icy-wind.description: The user attacks with a gust of chilled air. This also lowers opposing Pokémon's Speed stats.

tm-steel-wing.name: TM076: Steel Wing
tm-steel-wing.description: The target is hit with wings of steel. This may also raise the user's Defense stat.

tm-iron-tail.name: TM087: Iron Tail
tm-iron-tail.description: The target is slammed with a steel-hard tail. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tm-synthesis.name: TM089: Synthesis
tm-synthesis.description: The user restores its own HP. The amount of HP regained varies with the weather.

tm-hidden-power.name: TM090: Hidden Power
tm-hidden-power.description: A unique attack that varies in type depending on the Pokémon using it.

tm-crunch.name: TM093: Crunch
tm-crunch.description: The user crunches up the target with sharp fangs. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tm-future-sight.name: TM096: Future Sight
tm-future-sight.description: Two turns after this move is used, a hunk of psychic energy attacks the target.

tm-uproar.name: TM100: Uproar
tm-uproar.description: The user attacks in an uproar for three turns. During that time, no Pokémon can fall asleep.

tm-facade.name: TM105: Facade
tm-facade.description: This attack move doubles its power if the user is poisoned, burned, or paralyzed.

tm-revenge.name: TM114: Revenge
tm-revenge.description: This attack move's power is doubled if the user has been hurt by the opponent in the same turn.

tm-brick-break.name: TM115: Brick Break
tm-brick-break.description: The user attacks with a swift chop. It can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

tm-dive.name: TM120: Dive
tm-dive.description: Diving on the first turn, the user floats up and attacks on the next turn.

tm-blaze-kick.name: TM122: Blaze Kick
tm-blaze-kick.description: The user launches a kick that lands a critical hit more easily. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm-rock-tomb.name: TM130: Rock Tomb
tm-rock-tomb.description: Boulders are hurled at the target. This also lowers the target's Speed stat by preventing its movement.

tm-signal-beam.name: TM133: Signal Beam
tm-signal-beam.description: The user attacks with a sinister beam of light. This may also confuse the target.

tm-muddy-water.name: TM135: Muddy Water
tm-muddy-water.description: The user attacks by shooting muddy water at opposing Pokémon. This may also lower their accuracy.

tm-bullet-seed.name: TM136: Bullet Seed
tm-bullet-seed.description: The user forcefully shoots seeds at the target two to five times in a row.

tm-aerial-ace.name: TM137: Aerial Ace
tm-aerial-ace.description: The user confounds the target with speed, then slashes. This attack never misses.

tm-icicle-spear.name: TM138: Icicle Spear
tm-icicle-spear.description: The user launches sharp icicles at the target two to five times in a row.

tm-iron-defense.name: TM139: Iron Defense
tm-iron-defense.description: The user hardens its body's surface like iron, sharply raising its Defense stat.

tm-dragon-claw.name: TM140: Dragon Claw
tm-dragon-claw.description: The user slashes the target with huge sharp claws.

tm-bounce.name: TM143: Bounce
tm-bounce.description: The user bounces up high, then drops on the target on the second turn. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm-mud-shot.name: TM144: Mud Shot
tm-mud-shot.description: The user attacks by hurling a blob of mud at the target. This also lowers the target's Speed stat.

tm-poison-tail.name: TM145: Poison Tail
tm-poison-tail.description: The user hits the target with its tail. This may also poison the target. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-covet.name: TM146: Covet
tm-covet.description: The user endearingly approaches the target, then has a 30% chance to steal the target's held item.

tm-magical-leaf.name: TM147: Magical Leaf
tm-magical-leaf.description: The user scatters curious leaves that chase the target. This attack never misses.

tm-calm-mind.name: TM148: Calm Mind
tm-calm-mind.description: The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its spirit to raise its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

tm-dragon-dance.name: TM150: Dragon Dance
tm-dragon-dance.description: The user vigorously performs a mystic, powerful dance that raises its Attack and Speed stats.

tm-rock-blast.name: TM151: Rock Blast
tm-rock-blast.description: The user hurls hard rocks at the target. Two to five rocks are launched in a row.

tm-shock-wave.name: TM152: Shock Wave
tm-shock-wave.description: The user strikes the target with a quick jolt of electricity. This attack never misses.

tm-roost.name: TM154: Roost
tm-roost.description: The user lands and rests its body. This move restores the user's HP by up to half of its max HP.

tm-brine.name: TM157: Brine
tm-brine.description: If the target's HP is half or less, this attack will hit with double the power.

tm-pluck.name: TM158: Pluck
tm-pluck.description: The user pecks the target. If the target is holding a Berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.

tm-tailwind.name: TM159: Tailwind
tm-tailwind.description: The user whips up a turbulent whirlwind that ups the Speed stats of the user and its allies for four turns.

tm-u-turn.name: TM160: U-Turn
tm-u-turn.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tm-gastro-acid.name: TM166: Gastro Acid
tm-gastro-acid.description: The user hurls up its stomach acids on the target. The fluid eliminates the effect of the target's Ability.

tm-worry-seed.name: TM169: Worry Seed
tm-worry-seed.description: A seed that causes worry is planted on the target. It prevents sleep by making the target's Ability Insomnia.

tm-toxic-spikes.name: TM170: Toxic Spikes
tm-toxic-spikes.description: The user lays a trap of poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team. The spikes will poison opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

tm-aura-sphere.name: TM172: Aura Sphere
tm-aura-sphere.description: The user lets loose a blast of aura power from deep within its body at the target. This attack never misses.

tm-poison-jab.name: TM174: Poison Jab
tm-poison-jab.description: The target is stabbed with a tentacle, arm, or the like steeped in poison. This may also poison the target.

tm-dark-pulse.name: TM175: Dark Pulse
tm-dark-pulse.description: The user releases a horrible aura imbued with dark thoughts. This may also make the target flinch.

tm-aqua-tail.name: TM176: Aqua Tail
tm-aqua-tail.description: The user attacks by swinging its tail as if it were a vicious wave in a raging storm.

tm-seed-bomb.name: TM177: Seed Bomb
tm-seed-bomb.description: The user slams a barrage of hard-shelled seeds down on the target from above.

tm-air-slash.name: TM178: Air Slash
tm-air-slash.description: The user attacks with a blade of air that slices even the sky. This may also make the target flinch.

tm-x-scissor.name: TM179: X-Scissor
tm-x-scissor.description: The user slashes at the target by crossing its scythes or claws as if they were a pair of scissors.

tm-bug-buzz.name: TM180: Bug Buzz
tm-bug-buzz.description: The user generates a damaging sound wave by vibration. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-dragon-pulse.name: TM181: Dragon Pulse
tm-dragon-pulse.description: The target is attacked with a shock wave generated by the user's gaping mouth.

tm-power-gem.name: TM182: Power Gem
tm-power-gem.description: The user attacks with a ray of light that sparkles as if it were made of gemstones.

tm-drain-punch.name: TM183: Drain Punch
tm-drain-punch.description: An energy-draining punch. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

tm-focus-blast.name: TM185: Focus Blast
tm-focus-blast.description: The user heightens its mental focus and unleashes its power. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-energy-ball.name: TM186: Energy Ball
tm-energy-ball.description: The user draws power from nature and fires it at the target. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-giga-impact.name: TM189: Giga Impact
tm-giga-impact.description: The user charges at the target using every bit of its power. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm-avalanche.name: TM191: Avalanche
tm-avalanche.description: The power of this attack move is doubled if the user has been hurt by the target in the same turn.

tm-shadow-claw.name: TM192: Shadow Claw
tm-shadow-claw.description: The user slashes with a sharp claw made from shadows. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-thunder-fang.name: TM193: Thunder Fang
tm-thunder-fang.description: The user bites with electrified fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with paralysis.

tm-ice-fang.name: TM194: Ice Fang
tm-ice-fang.description: The user bites with cold-infused fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it frozen.

tm-fire-fang.name: TM195: Fire Fang
tm-fire-fang.description: The user bites with flame-cloaked fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with a burn.

tm-psycho-cut.name: TM196: Psycho Cut
tm-psycho-cut.description: The user tears at the target with blades formed by psychic power. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-zen-headbutt.name: TM197: Zen Headbutt
tm-zen-headbutt.description: The user focuses its willpower to its head and attacks the target. This may also make the target flinch.

tm-flash-cannon.name: TM198: Flash Cannon
tm-flash-cannon.description: The user gathers all its light energy and releases it all at once. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-rock-climb.name: TM199: Rock Climb
tm-rock-climb.description: The user attacks the target by smashing into it with incredible force. This may also confuse the target.

tm-cross-poison.name: TM205: Cross Poison
tm-cross-poison.description: A slashing attack with a poisonous blade that may also poison the target. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-iron-head.name: TM207: Iron Head
tm-iron-head.description: The user slams the target with its steel-hard head. This may also make the target flinch.

tm-bug-bite.name: TM211: Bug Bite
tm-bug-bite.description: The user bites the target. If the target is holding a Berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.

tm-charge-beam.name: TM212: Charge Beam
tm-charge-beam.description: The user attacks the target with an electric charge. The user may use any remaining electricity to raise its Sp. Atk stat.

tm-psyshock.name: TM215: Psyshock
tm-psyshock.description: The user materializes an odd psychic wave to attack the target. This attack does physical damage.

tm-venoshock.name: TM216: Venoshock
tm-venoshock.description: The user drenches the target in a special poisonous liquid. This move's power is doubled if the target is poisoned.

tm-heavy-slam.name: TM220: Heavy Slam
tm-heavy-slam.description: The user slams into the target with its heavy body. The more the user outweighs the target, the greater the move's power.

tm-electro-ball.name: TM221: Electro Ball
tm-electro-ball.description: The user hurls an electric orb at the target. The faster the user is than the target, the greater the move's power.

tm-flame-charge.name: TM222: Flame Charge
tm-flame-charge.description: Cloaking itself in flame, the user attacks the target. Then, building up more power, the user raises its Speed stat.

tm-low-sweep.name: TM223: Low Sweep
tm-low-sweep.description: The user makes a swift attack on the target's legs, which lowers the target's Speed stat.

tm-scald.name: TM230: Scald
tm-scald.description: The user shoots boiling hot water at its target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm-hex.name: TM231: Hex
tm-hex.description: This relentless attack does massive damage to a target affected by status conditions.

tm-incinerate.name: TM233: Incinerate
tm-incinerate.description: The user attacks opposing Pokémon with fire. If a Pokémon is holding a certain item, such as a Berry, the item becomes burned up and unusable.

tm-acrobatics.name: TM235: Acrobatics
tm-acrobatics.description: The user nimbly strikes the target. The fewer held items, the higher the damage it inflicts.

tm-retaliate.name: TM236: Retaliate
tm-retaliate.description: The user gets revenge for a fainted ally. If an ally fainted in the previous turn, this move's power is increased.

tm-water-pledge.name: TM237: Water Pledge
tm-water-pledge.description: A column of water hits the target. When used with its fire equivalent, its power increases and a rainbow appears.

tm-fire-pledge.name: TM238: Fire Pledge
tm-fire-pledge.description: A column of fire hits the target. When used with its grass equivalent, its power increases and a vast sea of fire appears.

tm-grass-pledge.name: TM239: Grass Pledge
tm-grass-pledge.description: A column of grass hits the target. When used with its water equivalent, its power increases and a vast swamp appears.

tm-volt-switch.name: TM240: Volt Switch
tm-volt-switch.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tm-bulldoze.name: TM242: Bulldoze
tm-bulldoze.description: The user strikes everything around it by stomping down on the ground. This lowers the Speed stats of those hit.

tm-frost-breath.name: TM243: Frost Breath
tm-frost-breath.description: The user blows its cold breath on the target. This attack always results in a critical hit.

tm-dragon-tail.name: TM244: Dragon Tail
tm-dragon-tail.description: The target is knocked away, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

tm-electroweb.name: TM246: Electroweb
tm-electroweb.description: The user attacks and captures opposing Pokémon using an electric net. This lowers their Speed stats.

tm-wild-charge.name: TM247: Wild Charge
tm-wild-charge.description: The user shrouds itself in electricity and smashes into its target. This also damages the user a little.

tm-drill-run.name: TM248: Drill Run
tm-drill-run.description: The user crashes into its target while rotating its body like a drill. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-razor-shell.name: TM250: Razor Shell
tm-razor-shell.description: The user cuts its target with sharp shells. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tm-heat-crash.name: TM251: Heat Crash
tm-heat-crash.description: The user slams its target with its flame-covered body. The more the user outweighs the target, the greater the move's power.

tm-tail-slap.name: TM252: Tail Slap
tm-tail-slap.description: The user attacks by striking the target with its hard tail. It hits the target two to five times in a row.

tm-petal-blizzard.name: TM256: Petal Blizzard
tm-petal-blizzard.description: The user stirs up a violent petal blizzard and attacks everything around it.

tm-disarming-voice.name: TM257: Disarming Voice
tm-disarming-voice.description: Letting out a charming cry, the user does emotional damage to opposing Pokémon. This attack never misses.

tm-draining-kiss.name: TM258: Draining Kiss
tm-draining-kiss.description: The user steals the target's HP with a kiss. The user's HP is restored by over half of the damage taken by the target.

tm-play-rough.name: TM261: Play Rough
tm-play-rough.description: The user plays rough with the target and attacks it. This may also lower the target's Attack stat.

tm-mystical-fire.name: TM263: Mystical Fire
tm-mystical-fire.description: The user attacks by breathing a special, hot fire. This also lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-power-up-punch.name: TM269: Power-Up Punch
tm-power-up-punch.description: Striking opponents over and over makes the user's fists harder. Hitting a target raises the Attack stat.

tm-darkest-lariat.name: TM270: Darkest Lariat
tm-darkest-lariat.description: The user swings both arms and hits the target. The target's stat changes don't affect this attack's damage.

tm-throat-chop.name: TM273: Throat Chop
tm-throat-chop.description: The user attacks the target's throat, and the resultant suffering prevents the target from using moves that emit sound for two turns.

tm-lunge.name: TM276: Lunge
tm-lunge.description: The user makes a lunge at the target, attacking with full force. This also lowers the target's Attack stat.

tm-smart-strike.name: TM278: Smart Strike
tm-smart-strike.description: The user stabs the target with a sharp horn. This attack never misses.

tm-psychic-fangs.name: TM281: Psychic Fangs
tm-psychic-fangs.description: The user bites the target with its psychic capabilities. This can also destroy Light Screen and Reflect.

tm-stomping-tantrum.name: TM282: Stomping Tantrum
tm-stomping-tantrum.description: Driven by frustration, the user attacks the target. If the user's previous move has failed, the power of this move doubles.

tm-breaking-swipe.name: TM285: Breaking Swipe
tm-breaking-swipe.description: The user swings its tough tail wildly and attacks opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Attack stats.

tm-expanding-force.name: TM287: Expanding Force
tm-expanding-force.description: The user attacks the target with its psychic power. This move's power goes up and damages all opposing Pokémon on Psychic Terrain.

tm-meteor-beam.name: TM290: Meteor Beam
tm-meteor-beam.description: In this two-turn attack, the user gathers space power and boosts its Sp. Atk stat, then attacks the target on the next turn.

tm-skitter-smack.name: TM295: Skitter Smack
tm-skitter-smack.description: The user skitters behind the target to attack. This also lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-burning-jealousy.name: TM296: Burning Jealousy
tm-burning-jealousy.description: The user attacks with energy from jealousy. This leaves all opposing Pokémon that have had their stats boosted during the turn with a burn.

tm-lash-out.name: TM297: Lash Out
tm-lash-out.description: The user lashes out to vent its frustration toward the target. If the user's stats were lowered during this turn, the power of this move is doubled.

tm-scorching-sands.name: TM304: Scorching Sands
tm-scorching-sands.description: The user throws scorching sand at the target to attack. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm-tera-blast.name: TM305: Tera Blast
tm-tera-blast.description: If the user has Terastallized, it unleashes energy of its Tera Type. This move inflicts damage using the Attack or Sp. Atk stat-whichever is higher for the user.

tm-ice-spinner.name: TM306: Ice Spinner
tm-ice-spinner.description: The user covers its feet in thin ice and twirls around, slamming into the target. This move's spinning motion also destroys the terrain.

tm-hard-press.name: TM311: Hard Press
tm-hard-press.description: The target is crushed with an arm, a claw, or the like to inflict damage. The more HP the target has left, the greater the move's power.

tm-alluring-voice.name: TM313: Alluring Voice
tm-alluring-voice.description: The user attacks the target using its angelic voice. This also confuses the target if its stats have been boosted during the turn.

tm-temper-flare.name: TM314: Temper Flare
tm-temper-flare.description: Spurred by desperation, the user attacks the target. This move's power is doubled if the user's previous move failed.

tm-supercell-slam.name: TM315: Supercell Slam
tm-supercell-slam.description: The user electrifies its body and drops onto the target to inflict damage. If this move misses, the user takes damage instead.

tm-psychic-noise.name: TM316: Psychic Noise
tm-psychic-noise.description: The user attacks the target with unpleasant sound waves. For two turns, the target is prevented from recovering HP through moves, Abilities, or held items.

tm-pay-day.name: TM002: Pay Day
tm-pay-day.description: Numerous coins are hurled at the target to inflict damage. Money is earned after the battle.

tm-double-edge.name: TM012: Double-Edge
tm-double-edge.description: A reckless, life-risking tackle in which the user rushes the target. This also damages the user quite a lot.

tm-flamethrower.name: TM015: Flamethrower
tm-flamethrower.description: The target is scorched with an intense blast of fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm-hydro-pump.name: TM016: Hydro Pump
tm-hydro-pump.description: The target is blasted by a huge volume of water launched under great pressure.

tm-surf.name: TM017: Surf
tm-surf.description: The user attacks everything around it by swamping its surroundings with a giant wave.

tm-ice-beam.name: TM018: Ice Beam
tm-ice-beam.description: The target is struck with an icy-cold beam of energy. This may also leave the target frozen.

tm-blizzard.name: TM019: Blizzard
tm-blizzard.description: A howling blizzard is summoned to strike opposing Pokémon. This may also leave the opposing Pokémon frozen.

tm-hyper-beam.name: TM021: Hyper Beam
tm-hyper-beam.description: The target is attacked with a powerful beam. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm-solar-beam.name: TM025: Solar Beam
tm-solar-beam.description: In this two-turn attack, the user gathers light, then blasts a bundled beam on the next turn.

tm-thunderbolt.name: TM027: Thunderbolt
tm-thunderbolt.description: A strong electric blast crashes down on the target. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm-thunder.name: TM029: Thunder
tm-thunder.description: A wicked thunderbolt is dropped on the target to inflict damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm-earthquake.name: TM030: Earthquake
tm-earthquake.description: The user sets off an earthquake that strikes every Pokémon around it.

tm-psychic.name: TM033: Psychic
tm-psychic.description: The target is hit by a strong telekinetic force. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-fire-blast.name: TM045: Fire Blast
tm-fire-blast.description: The target is attacked with an intense blast of all-consuming fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm-leech-life.name: TM050: Leech Life
tm-leech-life.description: The user drains the target's blood. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

tm-tri-attack.name: TM055: Tri Attack
tm-tri-attack.description: The user strikes with a simultaneous three-beam attack. This may also burn, freeze, or paralyze the target.

tm-sludge-bomb.name: TM065: Sludge Bomb
tm-sludge-bomb.description: Unsanitary sludge is hurled at the target. This may also poison the target.

tm-outrage.name: TM069: Outrage
tm-outrage.description: The user rampages and attacks for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

tm-giga-drain.name: TM071: Giga Drain
tm-giga-drain.description: A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by half the damage taken by the target.

tm-return.name: TM080: Return
tm-return.description: This full-power attack grows more powerful the more the user likes its Trainer.

tm-megahorn.name: TM084: Megahorn
tm-megahorn.description: Using its tough and impressive horn, the user rams into the target with no letup.

tm-shadow-ball.name: TM095: Shadow Ball
tm-shadow-ball.description: The user hurls a shadowy blob at the target. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-heat-wave.name: TM101: Heat Wave
tm-heat-wave.description: The user attacks by exhaling hot breath on opposing Pokémon. This may also leave those Pokémon with a burn.

tm-superpower.name: TM112: Superpower
tm-superpower.description: The user attacks the target with great power. However, this also lowers the user's Attack and Defense stats.

tm-knock-off.name: TM116: Knock Off
tm-knock-off.description: The user slaps down the target's held item, and that item can't be used in that battle. The move does more damage if the target has a held item.

tm-hyper-voice.name: TM123: Hyper Voice
tm-hyper-voice.description: The user lets loose a horribly echoing shout with the power to inflict damage.

tm-blast-burn.name: TM124: Blast Burn
tm-blast-burn.description: The target is razed by a fiery explosion. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm-hydro-cannon.name: TM125: Hydro Cannon
tm-hydro-cannon.description: The target is hit with a watery blast. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm-overheat.name: TM129: Overheat
tm-overheat.description: The user attacks the target at full power. The attack's recoil harshly lowers the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-frenzy-plant.name: TM141: Frenzy Plant
tm-frenzy-plant.description: The user slams the target with the roots of an enormous tree. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm-leaf-blade.name: TM149: Leaf Blade
tm-leaf-blade.description: The user handles a sharp leaf like a sword and attacks by cutting its target. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-close-combat.name: TM161: Close Combat
tm-close-combat.description: The user fights the target up close without guarding itself. This also lowers the user's Defense and Sp. Def stats.

tm-flare-blitz.name: TM171: Flare Blitz
tm-flare-blitz.description: The user cloaks itself in fire and charges the target. This also damages the user quite a lot. This attack may leave the target with a burn.

tm-brave-bird.name: TM187: Brave Bird
tm-brave-bird.description: The user tucks in its wings and charges from a low altitude. This also damages the user quite a lot.

tm-earth-power.name: TM188: Earth Power
tm-earth-power.description: The user makes the ground under the target erupt with power. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm-draco-meteor.name: TM202: Draco Meteor
tm-draco-meteor.description: Comets are summoned down from the sky onto the target. The attack's recoil harshly lowers the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-leaf-storm.name: TM203: Leaf Storm
tm-leaf-storm.description: The user whips up a storm of leaves around the target. The attack's recoil harshly lowers the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm-power-whip.name: TM204: Power Whip
tm-power-whip.description: The user violently whirls its vines, tentacles, or the like to harshly lash the target.

tm-gunk-shot.name: TM206: Gunk Shot
tm-gunk-shot.description: The user shoots filthy garbage at the target to attack. This may also poison the target.

tm-stone-edge.name: TM208: Stone Edge
tm-stone-edge.description: The user stabs the target from below with sharpened stones. Critical hits land more easily.

tm-grass-knot.name: TM210: Grass Knot
tm-grass-knot.description: The user snares the target with grass and trips it. The heavier the target, the greater the move's power.

tm-sludge-wave.name: TM219: Sludge Wave
tm-sludge-wave.description: The user strikes everything around it by swamping the area with a giant sludge wave. This may also poison those hit.

tm-foul-play.name: TM225: Foul Play
tm-foul-play.description: The user turns the target's power against it. The higher the target's Attack stat, the greater the damage it deals.

tm-sacred-sword.name: TM249: Sacred Sword
tm-sacred-sword.description: The user attacks by slicing with a long horn. The target's stat changes don't affect this attack's damage.

tm-hurricane.name: TM253: Hurricane
tm-hurricane.description: The user attacks by wrapping its opponent in a fierce wind that flies up into the sky. This may also confuse the target.

tm-phantom-force.name: TM255: Phantom Force
tm-phantom-force.description: The user vanishes somewhere, then strikes the target on the next turn. This move hits even if the target protects itself.

tm-dazzling-gleam.name: TM267: Dazzling Gleam
tm-dazzling-gleam.description: The user damages opposing Pokémon by emitting a powerful flash.

tm-high-horsepower.name: TM271: High Horsepower
tm-high-horsepower.description: The user fiercely attacks the target using its entire body.

tm-solar-blade.name: TM272: Solar Blade
tm-solar-blade.description: In this two-turn attack, the user gathers light and fills a blade with the light's energy, attacking the target on the next turn.

tm-pollen-puff.name: TM274: Pollen Puff
tm-pollen-puff.description: The user attacks the enemy with a pollen puff that explodes. If the target is an ally, it gives the ally a pollen puff that restores its HP instead.

tm-liquidation.name: TM283: Liquidation
tm-liquidation.description: The user slams into the target using a full-force blast of water. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tm-body-press.name: TM284: Body Press
tm-body-press.description: The user attacks by slamming its body into the target. The higher the user's Defense, the more damage it can inflict on the target.

tm-steel-beam.name: TM286: Steel Beam
tm-steel-beam.description: The user fires a beam of steel that it collected from its entire body. This also damages the user.

tm-scale-shot.name: TM289: Scale Shot
tm-scale-shot.description: The user attacks by shooting scales two to five times in a row. This move boosts the user's Speed stat but lowers its Defense stat.

tm-poltergeist.name: TM298: Poltergeist
tm-poltergeist.description: The user attacks the target by controlling the target's item. The move fails if the target doesn't have an item.
